  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to test the routine feasibility of an image tool adapted from
      the WELCH questionnaire ( Walking estimated limitation calculated by history) to estimate
      walking impairment (The WELSH questionnaire: Walking estimated limitation stated by history)
      in patients investigated for walking impairment. Secondary aims correlation with the maximal
      walking distance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The WELSH is self completed by the patients and scored by the physician after
      self-completion. Patients perform a 6 minutes walking test on a 30m corridor
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
